    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i hear the \"long term\" thing all the time but for a shop with like 15 employees, these costs aren't just some \"trade-off,\" they're often what kills the business. can u dig into the actual specific costs they face? like specifically how much it hits their bottom line compared to the actual benefits they're seeing?",
